&lt;p&gt;Potentially, more of these could be made to more closely match the Rust API, but I think this is enough to get the desired effect. Something that im keen to try out myself is a &lt;code&gt;TRY&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; macro to emulate the effect of Rust’s &lt;code&gt;?&lt;&#x2F;code&gt; operator. However, Im not sure how possible that is whilst taking into consideration its usage as an expression and not a statement.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
